article.headline: Delaware 76, Drexel 64
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Harding Nana had a career-high 28 points and pulled down 10 rebounds as Delaware closed out the regular season with a 76-64 win over Drexel on Saturday night. Delaware (16-11, 10-8 Colonial Athletic Association) jumped out to a 30-21 halftime lead and held off Drexel for the win. Rulon Washington came off the bench to add 11 points for the Hens, while Robin Wentt pulled down 13 rebounds and Mike Slattery and Mike Ames each had 11 points. The Dragons (18-9, 13-5) were led by Tim Whitworth, who had 22 points, including 15 in the first half when he connected on five 3-pointers. Jeremiah King added 15 points and eight assists. The Blue Hens had a 8-2 run that gave them a 21-12 lead with 7:04 left. Washington started the spurt with a 3-pointer and later added a layup for the Hens. A quick start in the second half for the Hens upped the lead to 13 points at 37-24 as Nana scored five points in the first four minutes. Drexel rallied and cut the lead to five points several times, pulling to within 42-37 with 11:59 remaining on two free throws by Jermaine Miller. But a 15-5 run that started on consecutive 3-pointers by Washington and Slattery and a dunk by Nana gave Delaware a 15-point lead at 57-42 with 7:48 left. Drexel never got closer than eight point for the rest of the game.
